FBIS4-13336 "drnes076_c_94012" FBIS-NES-94-076 Daily Report 15 Apr 1994 Egypt Jobs To Be Provided to `Repentant' Terrorists Jobs To Be Provided to `Repentant' Terrorists NC2004085894 Cairo AL-JUMHURIYAH in Arabic 15 Apr 94 p 1 NC2004085894 Cairo AL-JUMHURIYAH Arabic BFN [Text] A decision has been made to provide every repentant terrorist with a job. In fact, 25 repentant terrorists have been given jobs in Asyut, after it became evident that they were qualified and had university or high school diplomas that they had earned years ago. Dr. Yusuf Wali, secretary general of the National Democratic Party, made this statement. He also added that the party leaders in Asyut and Asyut Governor Samih Sa'id have been instructed to provide jobs immediately for repentant terrorists in the governorates.
